<article class="legal-page">
  <header class="legal-page__header">
    <p class="legal-page__eyebrow">PaymentReminder</p>
    <h1>PaymentReminder Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="legal-page__updated">Last updated: July 18, 2026</p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>1. Overview</h2>
    <p>
      PaymentReminder (the “Service,” “we,” “us”) provides an accounts-receivable reminder service
      for freelancers and small teams. These Terms of Service (“Terms”) govern your access to and
      use of the Service. By creating an account or using the Service, you agree to these Terms.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>2. Service Description</h2>
    <p>The Service:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Connects to Xero or Stripe to synchronize customer and invoice information.</li>
      <li>Organizes customers using payment-history rules and applies the reminder schedules you configure.</li>
      <li>Connects to a Gmail or Google Workspace account using the <code>gmail.send</code> permission so invoice reminders can be sent on your behalf.</li>
      <li>Records each reminder attempt and its delivery status so you can review reminder history.</li>
      <li>Processes your information according to our <%= link_to "Privacy Policy", privacy_path(script_name: nil) %>.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>3. Your Obligations</h2>
    <p>You agree to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Provide accurate information when configuring the Service.</li>
      <li>Maintain the security of your PaymentReminder, Xero, Stripe, and Google accounts.</li>
      <li>Comply with <a href="https://policies.google.com/terms">Google’s Terms of Service</a> and the <a href="https://developers.google.com/terms/api-services-user-data-policy">Google API Services User Data Policy</a>.</li>
      <li>Send reminders only to recipients you are legally entitled to contact. You are solely responsible for each reminder sent on your behalf.</li>
      <li>Comply with applicable anti-spam and email-marketing laws in your jurisdiction.</li>
      <li>Not use the Service to send unsolicited bulk email, phishing content, malware, or content that is illegal, deceptive, or harmful.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>4. Data Usage and Privacy</h2>
    <p>
      We handle information as described in our
      <%= link_to "Privacy Policy", privacy_path(script_name: nil) %>. In summary, the Service stores
      connected-service OAuth tokens, customer and invoice information, reminder settings, and
      reminder delivery records. We do not sell your information. Reminder recipients and message
      content are shared with Google only so Gmail can deliver the reminder you configured.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>5. Limitation of Liability</h2>
    <p>
      The Service is provided “as is” without warranty of any kind, express or implied. We do not
      guarantee uninterrupted or error-free synchronization or delivery of reminders. Delivery
